    <h3>@openhps/rdf</h3>
    {% markdown %}
        - RDF data model for OpenHPS
        - POSO integration
        - Serialisation and deserialisation
    {% endmarkdown %}
    <aside class="notes">
        Developers are not always eager to want to work with linked data to store information, especially for realtime applications
        such as positioning systems. This is why we created the @openhps/rdf package. It basically provides a mapping form
        the OpenHPS data model to RDF and back. This allows developers to easily store their data in a linked data format without
        specifically needing to know how linked data works. Furthermore, they can query the data is if they are querying 
        a MongoDB database, which is a lot more familiar to most developers.
    </aside>
</section>

