    <h3>@openhps/solid</h3>
    {% markdown %}
        - Solid storage and access control
        - Solid as a communication broker
    {% endmarkdown %}
    <aside class="notes">
        With the @openhps/rdf package we already had a way to store our data in a linked data format. However, if we talk about personal data
        or data that needs to be governed by a user, we also need a proper way to store this data. This is where the Solid project comes into place.

        For those who are unfamiliar with Solid, it is a project that allows users to store their data in a decentralised way. The data can be binary
        data, but also structured linked data. Users can assign access rights to the data so that only certain applications or users can access it.

        In addition to this, Solid offers specifications that enable applications to listen for changes in data - which is perfect for realtime applications
        such as positioning systems that want to use Solid as a communication broker.
    </aside>
</section>

